\[\dot{\mathbf{x}} =\mathbf{f}(\mathbf{x}),\ \mathbf{x}_{0}{=}\mathbf{x}(0), \tag{3a}\] \[y =q(\mathbf{x}), \tag{3b}\]

on a compact domain \(\mathbb{X}\subset\mathbb{R}^{d}\) with a quantity of interest \(q{\in}C(\mathbb{X})\). The above system class includes all systems with Lipschitz flow \(\mathbf{F}^{t}(\mathbf{x}_{0}):=\int_{0}^{t}\mathbf{f}(\mathbf{x}(\tau))d\tau\), e.g., mechanical systems [27].

Inspired by the spectral decomposition of Koopman operators, we look to replace the nonlinear state-space model (3) by an _LTI predictor_

